The <b>Grey-breasted Woodpecker</b> (<i>Melanerpes hypopolius</i>) is a species of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bird" title="Bird">bird</a> in the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Picidae" title="Picidae" class="mw-redirect">Picidae</a> family. It is <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Endemism" title="Endemism">endemic</a> to the interior of southwestern <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mexico" title="Mexico">Mexico</a>.
Its natural <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Habitat" title="Habitat">habitats</a> are subtropical or tropical moist lowland <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Forest" title="Forest">forests</a> and subtropical or tropical high-altitude <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Shrubland" title="Shrubland">shrubland</a>.
Like <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Gila_Woodpecker" title="Gila Woodpecker">Gila Woodpecker</a> (male has round red crown patch), but pale red on cheek; short black line over eye; much darker and grayer below and on head
<br />
